definitions.definition: A Sumerian goddess of sexual love , fertility , and warfare , known by the Akkadians as Ishtar and later identified with Astarte , Aphrodite , and Venus .

main_definition: ( mythology , Mesopotamian mythology ) A Sumerian goddess of sexual love , fertility , and warfare , known by the Akkadians as Ishtar and later identified with Astarte , Aphrodite , and Venus .
